BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:FBoAvpZ0sL2V9Z08Hiezr
SUMMARY:Paella Pop-Up
DTSTAMP:20260413T010450Z
DTSTART:20260421T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:You know us \\(or maybe you don't\\). We are obsessed with Nort
	hern Mediterranean cuisine. What is more quintessential than Paella when i
	t comes to Northern Mediterranean? \\(Well\, a few other dishes but paella
	 is certainly one of them\\). So\, join us for a very limited pop-up for a
	 seafood paella pop-up at a/stir. The ONLY option for dinner is\, you gues
	sed it\, paella. What is in it? This one will feature smoked chicken thigh
	s\, mussels\, shrimp and chorizo \\(no\, we won't forget the saffron\, oni
	on and the bell peppers\\). No vegan or vegetarian options this time aroun
	d. \n\nWhat else comes with it? A glass of Spanish wine - white or red\, y
	our choice. \n\nAnything else? Well\, if you so choose\, you will be able 
	to order a side salad and a basque cheesecake as dessert \\(neither are in
	cluded in price\, and both in very limited quantities\\). \n\nSeatings at 
	6pm\, 7pm or 8pm. Choose carefully. :-\\)\n\nPrice? $50/person\, inclusive
	 of taxes and gratuity. Includes a generous portion of paella and a 5 oz g
	lass of delicious Spanish wine. Salad and Basque cheesecake optionally ava
	ilable at the restaurant at time of dinner.\n\nFINE PRINT\n\nSince this is
	 a pop-up\, we cannot make any accommodations and substitutions with food 
	content. There will NOT be any other regular menu items on the day of serv
	ice - this is a pop-up for PAELLA only.\n\nNot a drinker? Don't wanna pay 
	for the wine? Consider joining us at another pop-up event. Since this is s
	uch a limited and narrow scope engagement\, we are not in a position to ac
	commodate requests.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/paell
	a-pop-up/18566854/2026-04-20T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/paella-pop-up/18566854/20
	26-04-20T00
LOCATION:Capitol Cider\, 818 E Pike St\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
